        <briefdescription>
<para>Compares this event to another for priority queue ordering. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Primary sort is by <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1_1_sim_event_1a607c1c72df770a64614efd6de3cd4698" kindref="member">Time</ref> ascending. When two events share the same time, <ref refid="class_assets_1_1_scripts_1_1_scheduling_1_1_core_1_1_sim_event_1ab56cee8678fd0b8f95a8aa4b18bf4fc8" kindref="member">SequenceNumber</ref> is used as a FIFO tiebreaker, ensuring earlier-enqueued events are processed first.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>other</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The event to compare against. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>A negative value if this event should be processed before <computeroutput>other</computeroutput>, zero if they are equal, or a positive value if <computeroutput>other</computeroutput> has higher priority. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
